[2026-07-23T11:33:17+02:00] USER_INPUT: Please consider this project. The main problem is that at the moment when I come out of a locked session I have to push <TAB> to get to the password section — I'd like it to go back to wherever I was before so that I can quickly just push `c` to copy a password I was using, rather than having to <tab> then scroll back down to the correct password. Does that make sense?
[2026-07-23T11:33:56+02:00] DECISION: Analyzed codebase and identified user request details.
1. When unlocking the vault, focus should automatically be placed on the ListView `#names` (password section).
2. When locking/unlocking the vault, the last selected credential name should be preserved, so that upon re-unlocking, the Vault screen selects the exact entry the user was previously viewing instead of defaulting to the top item.
